  "prompt": "What is the best book for learning angular 2?",
  "response": "Here are some highly recommended books for learning Angular 2 (and subsequent versions):\n\n1. \"Angular: Up and Running\" by Shyam Seshadri\n- Good for beginners\n- Covers core concepts clearly\n- Practical examples\n\n2. \"ng-book: The Complete Book on Angular\" by Nate Murray, Felipe Coury, et al.\n- Comprehensive coverage\n- Detailed explanations\n- Regularly updated\n- Most recommended by developers\n\n3. \"Angular Development with TypeScript\" by Yakov Fain and Anton Moiseev\n- Strong TypeScript focus\n- In-depth technical details\n- Good for developers wanting to understand underlying concepts\n\n4. \"Pro Angular\" by Adam Freeman\n- Advanced topics\n- Detailed technical explanations\n- Suitable for experienced developers\n\n5. \"Angular in Action\" by Jeremy Wilken\n- Practical approach\n- Real-world examples\n- Good for hands-on learning\n\nOnline Resources (Bonus):\n- Official Angular documentation\n- Angular.io tutorials\n- Udemy courses\n- YouTube tutorials\n\nRecommendation:\n- For beginners: \"Angular: Up and Running\" or \"ng-book\"\n- For experienced developers: \"Pro Angular\" or \"Angular Development with TypeScript\"\n\nNote: Angular evolves quickly, so always check for the most recent edition.",
